Text: IMPORTANT Actions this evening Cc In preparation for the upcoming move to Enron Center South we are moving your Home Directories to a new trading cluster WHAT YOU NEED TO DO This will occur for you this EVENING after PM We will need to restart your computer in order to complete this action Please log out or your computer by PM if the machine is not logged off we will reboot the machine in order to complete these actions Save your data before going home this evening If you have outstanding circumstances that we should address please reply to this email and we will change our schedule accordingly HERE ARE A FEW OF THE BENEFITS OF THIS ACTION Newer more stable environment More disk space available for common data Faster network connections HOW THIS WILL EFFECT YOU If you are a laptop user and have to work at home you should save any work to your C drive on the laptop DO NOT use the My Documents folder When you return to work and reconnect to the network any changes made to filesfolders in the My Documents folder may be deleted from the laptop Laptops reconnecting to the network for the first time will receive a synchronization error RESOLUTION Please call the Resolution Center x and they will correct the problem ASAP We will have additional Technicians available on the floor if the Resolution Center has any problems

RE hr phone Cc I am working with the David Cummings to lock down the timing and details on the numbers We are creating a new MAPP PC and getting it tested this week We will move the MAPP Printer over on Monday morning at AM We are deploying the machines EBA D that will be used for weekend work to the st floor today We will take the users original machine and predeploy it Genco operations are totally up and running The following systems have been setup and tested at ECS New ops old ops console new charts old MAIN ECAR Programmer console Corp machines I am putting together a full sheet with all of these details I will get out by tomorrow morning Lloyd If you want me to change anything let me know Thank you all for the help Daniel Original Message From Will Lloyd Sent Monday November AM To Muschar Daniel Baughman Jr Don Black Tamara Jae Cc Comeaux Keith Baughman Edward D May Tom Forney John M Thomas Paul D Subject RE hr phone Real time hour and Genco Services How will the cutover work If a trader operator logins in at the new building will the numbers not follow If so then we will bring in an extra crew at noon to login and get set up in the new building with a planned cut over around pm Once the transfer is done you will relocate the mapp equipment as well as the remaining ercot midwest southeast and northeast equipment to the new building The night shift will report to the new building at pm Thanks Original Message From Muschar Daniel Sent Monday November AM To Baughman Jr Don Black Tamara Jae Will Lloyd Subject hr phone TJ How many phone numbers does power have If any other than Hr trading please advise What is the number for HR group I will need to coordinate a cutover for this Do you know of any special phone needs for the weekend trading The people on turrets will be fine they pin in anywhere Any other thoughts or concerns are appreciated Thank you Daniel A Muschar ECS Project Team Lead Office Cell CCNA MCSE CNA A

physically separated from Estate not the literal nd day of ops spc Subject Final Project Expectations Issues File Project expectationsissuesxls

IMPORT EXPORT contactspst EXPORT your contacts Open Outlook and select the contacts folder Click on one of your contacts and then press CTRL A this will select all Press FILE Import and Export Choose EXPORT TO A FILE and press next Choose MICROSOFT EXCEL as the type and press next Make sure CONTACTS is selected and press next Choose a location to save the file to cKevinContactsxls then press next Press FINISH and it will take a minute to copy all contacts to an excel file Now you may want to open the excel file to make sure it has something in it then send it via email to your home IMPORT your contacts Detach the Excel file you got in email Save it to your hard drive and remember the location Open Outlook and choose FileImport and Export Choose Import from another program or file then press next Select Microsoft Excel from the list and press NEXT Choose the file you want to import The one you detached from email then press NEXT You can also choose whether to allow duplicate entries in case you have someone in both contact lists Select the Destination Folder Highlight Contacts and press NEXT You will see what actions will be completed press FINISH Now Outlook will import the files This will work from home and the office You can keep doing this every so often but remember to choose Do not allow duplicates in step of the IMPORT phase if you do this more than time Good Luck and let me know if you would like me to walk you through this Have a good day Daniel A Muschar Trader Support Group CCNA MCSE CNA A Pager Can also text page or

IMPORTANT Actions needed Tuesday Cc In preparation for the upcoming move to Enron Center South we are moving your Home Directories to a new trading cluster WHAT YOU NEED TO DO This will occur for you this EVENING after PM We will need to restart your computer in order to complete this action Please log out or your computer by PM if the machine is not logged off we will reboot the machine in order to complete these actions Save your data before going home this evening If you have outstanding circumstances and cannot be down please speak to the tech when he comes to your desk HERE ARE A FEW OF THE BENEFITS OF THIS ACTION Newer more stable environment More disk space available for common data Faster network connections HOW THIS WILL EFFECT YOU If you are a laptop user and have to work at home you should save any work to your C drive on the laptop DO NOT use the My Documents folder When you return to work and reconnect to the network any changes made to filesfolders in the My Documents folder may be deleted from the laptop Laptops reconnecting to the network for the first time will receive a synchronization error RESOLUTION Please call the Resolution Center x and they will correct the problem ASAP We will have additional Technicians available on the floor if the Resolution Center has any problems
